WEBVTT

00:01.376 --> 00:02.628
[ High‐pitched ringing ]

00:02.628 --> 00:04.213
[ Heartbeat ]

00:04.213 --> 00:07.216
[ Woman gasping ]

00:07.216 --> 00:08.842
♪♪

00:08.842 --> 00:11.345
Bailey:
[ Groaning, gasping ]

00:11.345 --> 00:12.513
Bailey?

00:12.513 --> 00:13.472
Bailey, you okay?

00:13.472 --> 00:15.224
[ Groaning ]

00:15.224 --> 00:17.017
Bailey.
Give me your belt.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.644
[ Radio beeps ]
Your belt. Give me your belt.

00:18.644 --> 00:20.187
Control, this is
Detective Lopez.

00:20.187 --> 00:21.772
I have a fully engulfed
structure fire

00:21.772 --> 00:24.233
at 1600 Quiet Valley Lane
in Newhall.

00:24.233 --> 00:26.026
I need fire rescue
and an RA

00:26.026 --> 00:28.028
for a woman with
a puncture wound
to her left leg.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.154
Fred's still in there.

00:29.154 --> 00:30.197
Don't move.

00:31.031 --> 00:33.450
[ Lopez and Bailey scream ]

00:33.450 --> 00:34.993
We have to help him!
Bailey.

00:34.993 --> 00:36.995
No one could have
survived that.

00:36.995 --> 00:39.706
Bailey, he's gone.

00:39.706 --> 00:43.293
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:43.293 --> 00:44.753
♪♪

00:47.756 --> 00:49.508
♪♪

00:52.052 --> 00:53.762
Hey, whoa, whoa!
What are you doing?

00:53.762 --> 00:54.972
I'm fine.
[ Groans ]

00:54.972 --> 00:55.973
You're not fine.
Come on.

00:55.973 --> 00:57.891
Back in bed.
Back in bed.

00:57.891 --> 00:58.684
[ Groans ]
Watch your legs.

00:58.684 --> 00:59.768
[ Knock on door ]

00:59.768 --> 01:00.686
How's the patient?

01:00.686 --> 01:01.979
Did they find Fred?

01:01.979 --> 01:03.522
I'm afraid so.

01:03.522 --> 01:07.401
His body sustained extensive
damage in the explosion,

01:07.401 --> 01:10.028
but the Deputy Fire Chief
made a positive ID.

01:10.028 --> 01:11.405
I'm sorry.
I know you were close.

01:11.405 --> 01:12.573
I thought we were.

01:12.573 --> 01:14.116
Then he turned out to be
a serial killer,

01:14.116 --> 01:16.660
so it would seem that
the guy I liked

01:16.660 --> 01:19.121
was just a disguise
he was wearing.

01:19.121 --> 01:20.831
Lopez: Seems like he knew
we were onto him ‐‐

01:20.831 --> 01:22.082
wanted to go out
on his own terms ‐‐

01:22.082 --> 01:23.584
one last fire.

01:23.584 --> 01:26.128
Hey, you okay?
I heard you got the guy.

01:26.128 --> 01:27.713
Thanks to Nolan
and Bailey.

01:27.713 --> 01:29.089
So we need to close out
the case tomorrow.

01:29.089 --> 01:30.507
Do you mind
partnering with Lopez?

01:30.507 --> 01:31.717
Yeah,
whatever you need.

01:31.717 --> 01:33.385
Sarge, I was hoping
I could take the day tomorrow,

01:33.385 --> 01:35.137
just to help Bailey
get settled at my place.

01:35.137 --> 01:36.763
I told you I'd be fine
in my apartment.

01:36.763 --> 01:38.515
I'm sure you would be,
but I'm not budging on this.

01:38.515 --> 01:39.850
I don't want to impose.

01:39.850 --> 01:41.852
It's not an imposition.

01:44.187 --> 01:46.148
[ Birds chirping ]

01:46.148 --> 01:49.526
Okay, here we go.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.194
Watch your step.

01:51.194 --> 01:52.738
You're pretty good
on those.

01:52.738 --> 01:54.823
Gymnast all through
high school and college.

01:54.823 --> 01:58.410
If you can sprain it, twist it,
or dislocate it, I have.

01:58.410 --> 02:00.287
All I want is a couch.

02:00.287 --> 02:01.538
You don't want to go
straight to bed?

02:01.538 --> 02:02.873
Not yet.

02:02.873 --> 02:06.168
First, I'm gonna have
a big cry and eat some carbs,

02:06.168 --> 02:07.919
probably cry again,

02:07.919 --> 02:08.920
then I can sleep.

02:08.920 --> 02:10.005
Okay.

02:10.005 --> 02:11.548
I will get the tissues
and ice cream.

02:14.301 --> 02:15.385
Thank you.

02:17.638 --> 02:18.889
You're welcome.

02:18.889 --> 02:23.143
♪♪

02:23.143 --> 02:25.187
So I rolled a stop sign.
What's the big deal?

02:25.187 --> 02:26.980
No, you ran a red light
and a stop sign,

02:26.980 --> 02:28.357
and when we tried to
pull you over,

02:28.357 --> 02:30.400
you flipped us off and led us on
a medium‐speed pursuit.

02:30.400 --> 02:33.362
I was late for an appointment
with Orchid, my life coach.

02:33.362 --> 02:34.821
Well, she's doing
a terrible job.

02:34.821 --> 02:36.365
Go stand over there.

02:36.365 --> 02:38.742
Is there anything we can do
about this lighting?

02:38.742 --> 02:39.826
[ Telephones ringing ]

02:39.826 --> 02:42.037
Hey, so I've been
meaning to talk to you

02:42.037 --> 02:44.122
about our bet
from the treasure hunt.

02:44.122 --> 02:46.416
The bet I won?
No, the bet I won.

02:46.416 --> 02:47.918
I had the gold
in my hands.

02:47.918 --> 02:50.379
Because I stopped to arrest
an armed gunman.

02:50.379 --> 02:52.005
Eh, technically,
I arrested him.

02:52.005 --> 02:54.508
All you did was stand there
with your arm out.

02:54.508 --> 02:55.801
Which is even more
impressive.

02:55.801 --> 02:56.968
[ Sighs ]

02:56.968 --> 02:58.136
Sir, what do you think?

02:58.136 --> 02:59.054
What?

02:59.054 --> 03:00.138
You okay, sir?

03:00.138 --> 03:01.139
Something wrong
with the booking slip?

03:01.139 --> 03:02.349
No. No.
What do you need?

03:02.349 --> 03:03.517
An umpire.

03:03.517 --> 03:05.977
Um, who do you think won
our treasure hunt bet?

03:05.977 --> 03:07.938
It was a tie.
Oh...

03:07.938 --> 03:10.107
We need a rematch.
Oh, I have an idea.

03:10.107 --> 03:11.900
Why don't we race each other
in an escape room?

03:11.900 --> 03:12.901
Hard pass.

03:12.901 --> 03:14.027
No,
we need a neutral party

03:14.027 --> 03:15.445
to decide the terms
of the competition.

03:15.445 --> 03:16.863
[ Door buzzes ]

03:18.115 --> 03:20.200
And that would be me.
Okay.

03:20.200 --> 03:23.120
I'm gonna assign each of you
a penal code violation

03:23.120 --> 03:24.746
at random.

03:24.746 --> 03:26.748
First one to make
their arrest wins.

03:26.748 --> 03:31.169
Officer Chen,
your crime is 266i ‐‐

03:31.169 --> 03:33.004
encourage, influence,
or persuade someone

03:33.004 --> 03:34.673
to become a prostitute.

03:34.673 --> 03:38.510
Sergeant Bradford,
yours is 148.4.

03:38.510 --> 03:39.803
Oh, come on.

03:39.803 --> 03:41.680
Willfully and maliciously
tampers with or breaks

03:41.680 --> 03:42.848
fire protection equipment?

03:42.848 --> 03:44.433
You knew that
off the top of your head?

03:44.433 --> 03:46.059
You didn't?

03:46.059 --> 03:47.602
Hmm.
It's unfair.

03:47.602 --> 03:49.229
So is life.
Deal with it.

03:50.105 --> 03:51.356
Hmm.

03:52.899 --> 03:54.401
Oh, thank you.

03:57.779 --> 03:59.197
[ Indistinct shouting ]

03:59.197 --> 04:01.158
Is there any way
I can get a single?

04:01.158 --> 04:02.576
No. I'm afraid not.

04:02.576 --> 04:03.702
Maybe I can make a donation

04:03.702 --> 04:05.120
to the policemen's fund
or something.

04:05.120 --> 04:06.663
Okay, don't add bribery
to your charge.

04:06.663 --> 04:07.873
It's a whole other
stack of paperwork.

04:07.873 --> 04:09.082
Let's go.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.042
[ Gasps ] What if I give you
someone worse?

04:11.042 --> 04:13.336
I know about
a real crime.

04:13.336 --> 04:15.130
I could cut a deal, right?

04:15.130 --> 04:16.256
Like in the movies.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.967
That depends.
What's the crime?

04:18.967 --> 04:21.636
They're alleging you beat a man
to death with a tire iron.

04:21.636 --> 04:23.930
Dude deserved it.
He's banging my ex‐wife.

04:23.930 --> 04:25.891
That's a street violation.
That demands repercussions.

04:25.891 --> 04:29.186
Right. Sadly, street violations
don't hold up in court.

04:29.186 --> 04:30.729
[ Scoffs ]
Says here
there's a witness.

04:30.729 --> 04:32.773
Yeah, some nosy old man
across the street

04:32.773 --> 04:34.232
saw the whole thing.

04:34.232 --> 04:35.942
Well, that's a problem.
Why?

04:35.942 --> 04:37.444
He's the one that's watching us
like some perv.

04:37.444 --> 04:39.488
Be that as it may, we should
start talking plea deal.

04:39.488 --> 04:40.781
A ‐‐ No!

04:40.781 --> 04:42.157
No way, man, okay?

04:42.157 --> 04:44.117
Elijah said
you could fix this.

04:44.117 --> 04:46.369
Elijah makes
too many promises.

04:47.662 --> 04:49.206
But I'll do what I can.

04:49.206 --> 04:51.541
In the meantime, hey,
you know the drill ‐‐

04:51.541 --> 04:52.793
best behavior.

04:52.793 --> 04:54.252
Don't talk to anyone.

04:54.252 --> 04:55.754
[ Telephone ringing ]

04:55.754 --> 04:57.422
I noticed you got
a new client.

04:58.423 --> 04:59.549
Yeah.

04:59.549 --> 05:00.634
Business is good.

05:00.634 --> 05:01.968
Lately, it seems like
all your clients

05:01.968 --> 05:03.762
are on Elijah Stone's payroll.

05:05.514 --> 05:08.725
Well, every criminal defendant
is entitled to a defense,

05:08.725 --> 05:11.311
regardless of who
they associate with.

05:11.311 --> 05:13.980
Yes, and up 'til recently,

05:13.980 --> 05:16.900
you've always chosen
to represent the underdog.

05:16.900 --> 05:18.819
But now, the way
things are going,

05:18.819 --> 05:20.654
you're on your way
to becoming a mob lawyer.

05:20.654 --> 05:22.823
[ Chuckles ]
I think that's a bit extreme.

05:22.823 --> 05:25.992
And there's only two ways
I've ever seen that turn out ‐‐

05:25.992 --> 05:28.995
you end up disbarred
and indicted

05:28.995 --> 05:30.580
or you end up dead.

05:30.580 --> 05:31.790
Okay, I think that ‐‐

05:34.709 --> 05:36.753
You know how much I care
for Angela.

05:36.753 --> 05:39.422
If you ever get in
over your head,

05:39.422 --> 05:40.799
you can come see me.

05:43.301 --> 05:45.720
I appreciate that.

05:45.720 --> 05:47.138
But you know
I would never do anything

05:47.138 --> 05:49.599
to jeopardize my family.

05:49.599 --> 05:51.226
I hope not.

05:51.226 --> 05:55.063
♪♪

05:55.063 --> 05:57.399
[ Door alarm buzzes ]

05:57.399 --> 05:59.776
I'll let you know if
there's gonna be a service.

05:59.776 --> 06:01.361
Okay, bye.

06:01.361 --> 06:03.113
[ Cellphone beeps ]

06:03.113 --> 06:04.447
I made breakfast.

06:04.447 --> 06:05.448
You sure did.

06:05.448 --> 06:07.367
I was feeling
a little powerless,

06:07.367 --> 06:08.869
so this happened.

06:08.869 --> 06:10.036
You're not gonna
hear me complaining.

06:10.036 --> 06:12.289
This smells amazing.

06:12.289 --> 06:13.331
Who was that
on the phone?

06:13.331 --> 06:14.666
Fred's old captain.

06:14.666 --> 06:16.251
His family's dealing
with so much,

06:16.251 --> 06:19.004
so I'm contacting some
of his former colleagues.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

06:19.004 --> 06:21.172
That's me.
I'll take this real quick.

06:21.172 --> 06:22.173
Hey, what's up?

06:22.173 --> 06:23.675
I just wanted to call
and check in

06:23.675 --> 06:25.051
and see how
Bailey's doing.

06:25.051 --> 06:27.178
Uh, she's made four
different kinds of pancakes.

06:27.178 --> 06:28.638
I'm not sure
if that's good or bad.

06:28.638 --> 06:31.516
Yeah, the type A personality's
first stage of grief ‐‐ cooking.

06:31.516 --> 06:33.518
What's next?
Uh, cleaning.

06:33.518 --> 06:35.186
Then organization.

06:35.186 --> 06:36.354
She can't fix what happened,

06:36.354 --> 06:37.898
but she can fix
every little thing

06:37.898 --> 06:39.232
that's wrong
in her apartment.

06:39.232 --> 06:40.317
Uh, well,
she's staying with me.

06:40.317 --> 06:42.527
Yeah, well,
when she changes the drapes,

06:42.527 --> 06:43.862
just roll with it.
Right.

06:43.862 --> 06:44.988
[ Snaps fingers ]

06:44.988 --> 06:47.073
Thanks for checking in.
I gotta go.

06:47.073 --> 06:48.617
[ Cellphone beeps ]

06:48.617 --> 06:50.869
I am so sorry, David,
but can you repeat that?

06:50.869 --> 06:53.038
When were you at Lake Mead
with Fred?

06:53.038 --> 06:54.247
David: Last Fourth of July.

06:54.247 --> 06:56.082
And you were with him
the whole time?
Yep.

06:56.082 --> 06:58.293
It was supposed to be
a week‐long camping trip,

06:58.293 --> 07:01.588
but, uh, a couple days in,
he got a nasty stomach bug.

07:01.588 --> 07:04.382
He got so dehydrated,
I had to take him to Henderson.

07:04.382 --> 07:06.217
He spent the rest of the trip
in the hospital.

07:06.217 --> 07:08.511
Never thought that'd be
the last time I'd ever see him.

07:08.511 --> 07:09.721
And he will be missed.

07:09.721 --> 07:11.014
I will let you know
if there's any details

07:11.014 --> 07:12.015
about the funeral.

07:12.015 --> 07:13.475
Take care, okay?
Thanks, Bailey.

07:13.475 --> 07:15.060
You too.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

07:15.060 --> 07:17.270
Okay, I know
I'm on pain pills and all,

07:17.270 --> 07:18.897
but you heard
what I just heard, right?

07:18.897 --> 07:21.691
We know Fred was in Nevada
July 8th,

07:21.691 --> 07:25.153
and that lined up
with an unsolved arson‐homicide.

07:25.153 --> 07:26.738
But he was in the hospital.

07:26.738 --> 07:28.114
Fred has an alibi.

07:28.114 --> 07:29.824
That means Fred was set up,

07:29.824 --> 07:31.910
and the real killer
is still out there somewhere.

07:31.910 --> 07:33.119
What about the watch

07:33.119 --> 07:34.829
and all the keepsakes
I found in his house?

07:34.829 --> 07:37.957
Whoever framed Fred
must have planted them there,

07:37.957 --> 07:39.000
counting on us
finding them.

07:39.000 --> 07:40.043
I gotta call Lopez,

07:40.043 --> 07:41.836
have her reopen
the investigation.

07:41.836 --> 07:42.837
Don't just call.

07:42.837 --> 07:44.381
You need to go into work.

07:44.381 --> 07:45.256
Find that bastard.

07:45.256 --> 07:46.466
Are you sure?

07:46.466 --> 07:48.093
We have a deal,
remember?

07:48.093 --> 07:49.427
I run toward fires.

07:49.427 --> 07:50.720
You run toward bullets.

07:50.720 --> 07:52.430
Time to run toward bullets.

07:53.723 --> 07:56.267
But not literally.

07:56.267 --> 07:57.644
Right.

07:57.644 --> 07:59.896
♪♪

08:03.608 --> 08:05.402
So, I have a list of locations
we should check out

08:05.402 --> 08:06.611
when we get back out
on patrol.

08:06.611 --> 08:08.822
You know, just some places
that I think need

08:08.822 --> 08:10.073
a police presence.

08:10.073 --> 08:12.325
Places you're sure to get
your pandering collar?

08:12.325 --> 08:14.953
Oh. Yeah. Maybe.

08:14.953 --> 08:16.871
Is that really your focus?

08:16.871 --> 08:19.332
Our bet?
Come on.

08:19.332 --> 08:20.667
I know that you bribed Nell

08:20.667 --> 08:23.962
to throw any "fire alarm
tampering" cases your way.

08:23.962 --> 08:25.797
Nell and I are friends.
Mm.

08:25.797 --> 08:27.382
Sometimes, I give her
Dodgers tickets.

08:27.382 --> 08:28.425
[ Scoffs ]

08:31.052 --> 08:32.721
Oh, finally.

08:32.721 --> 08:33.930
What's this all about?

08:33.930 --> 08:35.140
[ Sighs ]

08:35.140 --> 08:36.766
Mrs. Carter, I understand
that you've recently started

08:36.766 --> 08:38.059
your own skincare line.

08:38.059 --> 08:39.227
Yes.

08:39.227 --> 08:42.230
We're a small operation,
but we're growing.

08:42.230 --> 08:44.065
I'm hoping to get
a write‐up in Goop.

08:44.065 --> 08:45.942
I‐I don't know
what that is.

08:45.942 --> 08:47.027
I'll explain later.

08:47.027 --> 08:48.069
Uh, a friend of yours

08:48.069 --> 08:49.821
gave us a jar
of your night cream.

08:49.821 --> 08:51.281
She claims that
one of the ingredients

08:51.281 --> 08:53.033
is tiger's blood ‐‐
like, literally,

08:53.033 --> 08:54.868
blood from
an endangered animal.

08:54.868 --> 08:56.703
Firms the skin
right up.

08:56.703 --> 08:59.539
Participating in
the endangered animal trade

08:59.539 --> 09:01.541
could land you in jail
for up to five years.

09:01.541 --> 09:03.793
You don't understand
the wellness game.

09:03.793 --> 09:05.086
It's cutthroat.

09:05.086 --> 09:06.796
I need to stand out.

09:06.796 --> 09:08.089
How else am I gonna compete

09:08.089 --> 09:09.966
with Sloan
and her vitamin business?

09:09.966 --> 09:13.636
I mean, everybody knows that
her B‐12 rejuvenation pills

09:13.636 --> 09:16.890
are just benzos
in fancy bottles.

09:16.890 --> 09:18.516
♪♪

09:18.516 --> 09:21.311
Um, she's selling
psychiatric drugs?

09:21.311 --> 09:23.688
Oh, the whole
"westside buffet."

09:23.688 --> 09:25.273
What's Sloan's last name?

09:26.441 --> 09:28.193
Hey, any news?

09:28.193 --> 09:31.279
Valley Hospital in Henderson
verified that Fred was a patient

09:31.279 --> 09:32.614
from July 6th
to the 10th.

09:32.614 --> 09:33.740
Okay, so there's no way

09:33.740 --> 09:35.784
he committed the murder
and arson in Nevada.

09:35.784 --> 09:37.744
No, we're gonna have to go back
and re‐examine everything

09:37.744 --> 09:39.204
going back to the first
hit and run.

09:39.204 --> 09:40.955
Whoever did this
is covering his tracks,

09:40.955 --> 09:42.082
so we need to separate

09:42.082 --> 09:43.833
the things our killer
wanted us to believe

09:43.833 --> 09:45.168
from the facts
of the case.

09:45.168 --> 09:47.003
Hey, uh, Nolan.

09:47.003 --> 09:49.089
Oh, uh, brought this
for Bailey.

09:49.089 --> 09:50.590
Hope she's, uh,
f‐feeling better.

09:50.590 --> 09:51.883
Oh, thank you, that's ‐‐
that's very thoughtful.

09:51.883 --> 09:52.884
Yeah, she's doing great.

09:52.884 --> 09:54.552
Oh, uh, I brought that, uh,

09:54.552 --> 09:55.970
doorbell camera footage
you asked for.

09:55.970 --> 09:57.180
Right, thank you very much
for that.

09:57.180 --> 09:58.306
This is Marcus.

09:58.306 --> 09:59.724
He's, uh,
Fred's neighbor.

09:59.724 --> 10:00.767
I met him
at the barbecue.

10:00.767 --> 10:02.894
Uh, this is Detectives Lopez
and Harper.

10:02.894 --> 10:04.062
Good to meet you.

10:04.062 --> 10:05.438
I mean,
bad circumstances.

10:05.438 --> 10:07.816
I ‐‐ I don't know
what I'm trying to say.

10:07.816 --> 10:09.526
Yeah, we're all struggling
with what happened.

10:09.526 --> 10:10.777
Uh, what did happen?

10:10.777 --> 10:13.113
Uh, people were saying
that it was a gas leak,

10:13.113 --> 10:15.490
and one of the firefighters said
it could be arson.

10:15.490 --> 10:17.450
And now I'm standing
in a police station.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.119
I really don't know
what to think.

10:19.119 --> 10:21.287
Uh, well, I'm afraid
there's not much I can tell you.

10:21.287 --> 10:22.455
Of course. Right.

10:22.455 --> 10:24.249
Did you notice anything
out of the ordinary

10:24.249 --> 10:25.458
in the last few days?

10:25.458 --> 10:28.878
Other than a big ball
of fire, no. Sorry.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.713
Well, if you can think
of anything else,

10:30.713 --> 10:32.090
you have Nolan's number.

10:32.090 --> 10:33.842
Absolutely.

10:33.842 --> 10:35.260
Thanks again.
Yeah.

10:37.345 --> 10:38.346
What'd he get her?

10:38.346 --> 10:40.140
Uh...chocolates.

10:40.140 --> 10:41.432
That's nice.

10:41.432 --> 10:42.725
Look out.
[ Snickers ]

10:42.725 --> 10:43.768
What do you mean?
[ Scoffs ]

10:43.768 --> 10:45.687
Nolan, he was
the only civilian

10:45.687 --> 10:47.230
at the firefighter party.

10:47.230 --> 10:50.525
He is buying gifts
for Bailey.

10:50.525 --> 10:51.901
Come on.
He's a badge bunny.

10:51.901 --> 10:53.319
Just for
a different badge.

10:53.319 --> 10:55.113
And your girlfriend's
wearing it.

10:55.113 --> 10:56.489
Oh, no,
I don't think so.

10:56.489 --> 10:57.907
No, uh, he knows Bailey.

10:57.907 --> 10:59.159
It's not so weird.

10:59.159 --> 11:00.827
Okay, when was the last time
you bought chocolates

11:00.827 --> 11:02.954
for someone you weren't
sleeping with?

11:03.913 --> 11:05.415
Um...

11:05.415 --> 11:09.460
♪♪

11:09.460 --> 11:11.796
That guy's after
my girlfriend.
Mm. Yeah.

11:11.796 --> 11:12.797
Fun.

11:12.797 --> 11:14.090
Okay, I'm gonna start

11:14.090 --> 11:15.884
combing through
the security footage.

11:15.884 --> 11:16.968
What are you going to do?

11:16.968 --> 11:18.219
Oh, I'm, uh,
headed to the hospital.

11:18.219 --> 11:19.220
The victim you pulled
out of the fire

11:19.220 --> 11:20.638
is finally out of ICU.

11:20.638 --> 11:22.182
I'll go with you.
All right.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.057
Thank you.
Mm‐hmm.

11:23.057 --> 11:25.268
[ Car alarm chirps ]

11:27.020 --> 11:28.855
[ Sighs ]

11:28.855 --> 11:30.648
Elijah needs to see you.

11:30.648 --> 11:32.650
Sure.

11:32.650 --> 11:34.235
Just tell him to come upstairs.
We'll talk in my office.

11:34.235 --> 11:35.403
Nah.

11:35.403 --> 11:36.946
He wants to talk to you
in his.

11:39.199 --> 11:41.326
Counselor.

11:41.326 --> 11:43.203
[ Engine starts ]

11:43.203 --> 11:44.829
[ Chuckles ]

11:45.788 --> 11:47.624
[ Sighs ]

11:47.624 --> 11:49.209
Just heard from Jay.

11:49.209 --> 11:52.170
He expressed
a lack of confidence

11:52.170 --> 11:55.840
in your ability to get him out
of his legal difficulties.

11:55.840 --> 11:57.550
He murdered a man.

11:57.550 --> 11:58.718
Allegedly.

11:59.886 --> 12:01.554
Except for the eyewitness
that clearly saw it happen.

12:01.554 --> 12:03.514
Oh, come on, Counselor.

12:03.514 --> 12:05.099
Eyewitness misidentification

12:05.099 --> 12:08.478
is the leading cause
of wrongful conviction.

12:08.478 --> 12:10.104
That's Defense Attorney 101.

12:10.104 --> 12:11.481
What, I don't got enough
on my plate,

12:11.481 --> 12:13.107
I gotta do your job, too?

12:13.107 --> 12:14.901
Find some dirt on this guy.

12:14.901 --> 12:16.903
Make him seem unreliable.

12:16.903 --> 12:18.196
I'll do my best,
but so far, I ‐‐

12:18.196 --> 12:20.949
Look, Jay got sloppy.

12:21.908 --> 12:25.370
I know,
and I'm pissed about it.

12:25.370 --> 12:27.121
But he's my wife's
favorite cousin,

12:27.121 --> 12:29.207
which means
he's my favorite cousin,

12:29.207 --> 12:31.376
so prison's not an option.

12:31.376 --> 12:35.046
Now, either you make
the witness go away,

12:35.046 --> 12:36.547
or Moreno does.

12:36.547 --> 12:39.842
♪♪

12:39.842 --> 12:41.594
As in "rest in peace"?

12:41.594 --> 12:42.845
I didn't say that.

12:42.845 --> 12:44.514
Unlike my wife's
dumbass cousin,

12:44.514 --> 12:48.059
I'm not foolish enough
to commit or confess to crimes

12:48.059 --> 12:49.352
in front of witnesses.

12:49.352 --> 12:50.603
We don't even have to
go there, okay?

12:50.603 --> 12:51.854
I can handle this.

12:51.854 --> 12:54.232
I just need some time.
Get it done today.

12:54.232 --> 12:55.275
Meeting's over.

12:55.275 --> 12:57.277
Get out of my office
and go do your job.

12:57.277 --> 13:00.530
♪♪

13:00.530 --> 13:06.619
♪♪

13:06.619 --> 13:08.121
[ Sighs ]

13:08.121 --> 13:10.498
Tim: Take off your
sunglasses, ma'am.
Do I have to?

13:10.498 --> 13:12.458
These fluorescent lights
give me vertigo.

13:12.458 --> 13:14.335
Okay, that could be
the least of your worries.

13:14.335 --> 13:16.796
We've been informed that
you're selling psychiatric drugs

13:16.796 --> 13:17.797
as a vitamin.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.090
Who said that?
It doesn't matter.

13:19.090 --> 13:20.633
I'm helping people.

13:20.633 --> 13:21.801
What's the problem?

13:21.801 --> 13:23.594
You can't prescribe
a controlled substance

13:23.594 --> 13:24.762
without a medical license.

13:24.762 --> 13:26.306
My husband is a doctor.

13:26.306 --> 13:27.932
It's the family
prescription pad.

13:27.932 --> 13:29.767
Yeah, that's not a thing.

13:29.767 --> 13:31.311
Look, I don't think
you're hearing me, all right?

13:31.311 --> 13:32.645
This makes you
a drug dealer.

13:32.645 --> 13:34.856
And given the circumstances,
a pretty high level one.

13:34.856 --> 13:36.691
You could be looking at
20 years in prison.

13:36.691 --> 13:39.277
What? No.
No, no, no, no, no.

13:39.277 --> 13:42.488
This wh‐‐ This whole thing has
gotten horribly out of hand.

13:42.488 --> 13:43.906
Who ratted me out, anyway?

13:45.491 --> 13:46.868
It was Aston, wasn't it?

13:46.868 --> 13:48.286
She's been trying
to take me down

13:48.286 --> 13:49.954
ever since I stole
her portrait painter.

13:49.954 --> 13:51.539
Like she needs to be
hung on a wall.

13:51.539 --> 13:53.499
You want a real crime
to chase?

13:53.499 --> 13:55.418
Aston's trying to hire
a hitman.

13:56.335 --> 13:58.129
W‐What do you mean?

13:58.129 --> 14:00.048
Her husband's worth more
dead than alive,

14:00.048 --> 14:01.549
so she's been
on the dark web

14:01.549 --> 14:03.384
trying to hire someone
to kill him.

14:03.384 --> 14:05.178
[ Sighs ]

14:05.178 --> 14:06.179
[ Sighs ]

14:09.724 --> 14:11.476
♪♪

14:11.476 --> 14:12.852
[ Rapping ] ♪ Yah ♪

14:14.479 --> 14:15.855
♪ Yah, yah, yah ♪

14:15.855 --> 14:18.357
Okay. Oh.
That's your disguise?

14:18.357 --> 14:19.484
You don't even look
like a hitman.

14:19.484 --> 14:21.277
You just look like you.

14:21.277 --> 14:23.029
This is what real hitmen
look like.

14:23.029 --> 14:24.697
That is not the point.

14:24.697 --> 14:26.407
Come on. Get in.

14:26.407 --> 14:28.451
♪ Woke up trying to work
the muscles ♪
[ Sighs ]

14:28.451 --> 14:30.787
What I'm wearing is fine.
Okay.

14:30.787 --> 14:32.789
Third rule
of undercover work ‐‐

14:32.789 --> 14:33.998
know your audience.

14:33.998 --> 14:36.501
You are not trying to fool
another criminal.

14:36.501 --> 14:38.920
You're trying to fool a woman
who gets her ideas about crime

14:38.920 --> 14:40.546
from Lifetime movies.

14:40.546 --> 14:41.714
Put it on.

14:41.714 --> 14:42.840
Fine.

14:42.840 --> 14:43.841
Thank you.

14:43.841 --> 14:45.635
♪ Tryin' new...in the lab ♪

14:45.635 --> 14:47.678
♪ Got the flow down
to a science ♪

14:47.678 --> 14:49.597
[ Sighs ]
Oh, my gosh.

14:49.597 --> 14:51.641
Yeah, that's much better.
[ Sighs ]

14:51.641 --> 14:53.309
I look like an idiot.

14:53.309 --> 14:54.560
I'd pull me over
in a heartbeat.

14:54.560 --> 14:56.395
Exactly ‐‐ because
you look the part.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.231
♪ I'm tryna get rich,
yeah, I'm tryna make moves ♪

14:58.231 --> 14:59.607
♪ Yeah, I'm tryna find vibes ♪
All right, mic me up.

14:59.607 --> 15:00.858
Let's get this over with.

15:00.858 --> 15:02.193
♪ Prove that the flow
too smooth ♪

15:02.193 --> 15:04.070
♪ Like butter, ooh‐ooh,
now what you gone do ♪

15:04.070 --> 15:06.072
♪ When the crew come through
hit you with the one‐two ♪

15:06.072 --> 15:07.448
It's a little too high.

15:07.448 --> 15:08.533
♪ With my...Lamar ♪

15:08.533 --> 15:09.617
I know what I'm doing.
[ Tape rips ]

15:09.617 --> 15:10.868
[ High‐pitched ] Ow.

15:10.868 --> 15:12.078
♪ I'll tell you what it is ♪

15:12.078 --> 15:13.287
Sorry.

15:13.287 --> 15:15.206
Mic check, one, two.

15:15.206 --> 15:16.249
Okay, levels are good.

15:16.249 --> 15:18.126
She should be here
in 15 minutes.

15:18.126 --> 15:20.711
♪ Yeah, right now, right now ♪

15:20.711 --> 15:22.380
♪ I'm coming for it all
right now ♪

15:22.380 --> 15:24.132
♪ Doesn't matter
who what when where how ♪
[ Sliding door opens ]

15:24.132 --> 15:26.759
♪♪

15:29.804 --> 15:32.723
[ Car horn honks in distance ]

15:32.723 --> 15:35.560
♪ Pimpin' if you gotta know,
and you really wanna know ♪

15:35.560 --> 15:36.769
What are you doing here?

15:36.769 --> 15:38.229
I have until
the end of the day.

15:38.229 --> 15:39.772
I'm just here to get it done
if you can't.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.315
Good luck.

15:41.315 --> 15:44.610
♪ And ya know a playa stayin'
keyed the Cali way ♪

15:44.610 --> 15:46.362
♪ Break it down
then you bring it back ♪

15:46.362 --> 15:48.239
[ Music continues, muffled ]

15:48.239 --> 15:49.407
[ Knock on door ]

15:50.700 --> 15:53.494
Mr. Andrews, thank you for
meeting me on such short notice.

15:55.288 --> 15:57.290
Long as I ain't gotta
drive nowhere.

16:00.084 --> 16:02.128
So, I just have
a few questions [Sighs]

16:02.128 --> 16:03.963
about the crime ‐‐
thank you ‐‐

16:03.963 --> 16:05.673
that you allegedly
witnessed.

16:05.673 --> 16:08.134
Uh, first,
do you wear glasses?

16:08.134 --> 16:09.969
20/20 vision
my whole life.

16:10.970 --> 16:12.013
Great.

16:13.431 --> 16:15.349
Anything to drink
on the night in question?

16:15.349 --> 16:17.185
Been sober 38 years.

16:20.021 --> 16:23.399
How clear was your view
of the events

16:23.399 --> 16:24.734
the night in question?

16:24.734 --> 16:27.612
He killed the man
right there.

16:27.612 --> 16:28.696
Huh?

16:33.701 --> 16:34.869
It was getting late ‐‐
8:00 p. m.

16:34.869 --> 16:37.663
It would've been dark.
Not on my block.

16:37.663 --> 16:41.000
Those street lights so much
as flicker, I call the city.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.294
You know why, Mr. Evers?

16:43.294 --> 16:46.255
'Cause I do whatever it takes
to protect my neighborhood.

16:46.255 --> 16:47.632
From criminals.

16:48.591 --> 16:51.219
And their lawyers.

16:51.219 --> 16:53.221
I know why you're here.

16:53.221 --> 16:55.389
Wanna scare me off.
[ Chuckles ]

16:55.389 --> 16:58.267
Well, go tell your boss...

16:58.267 --> 16:59.810
I don't scare easy.

17:01.520 --> 17:03.105
I'm not trying
to intimidate you.

17:03.105 --> 17:04.690
I just, um...

17:08.236 --> 17:09.695
[ Sighs ]

17:09.695 --> 17:11.030
I hear you.

17:15.159 --> 17:17.370
Can I use your bathroom
before I go?

17:17.370 --> 17:18.579
Sure.

17:20.164 --> 17:21.374
Thank you.

17:21.374 --> 17:29.966
♪♪

17:29.966 --> 17:38.558
♪♪

17:38.558 --> 17:47.191
♪♪

17:47.191 --> 17:55.783
♪♪

17:55.783 --> 17:57.785
[ Dog barking in distance ]

17:57.785 --> 18:00.204
♪♪

18:00.204 --> 18:01.706
[ Dial tone ]

18:01.706 --> 18:03.124
[ Keypad beeping ]

18:03.124 --> 18:04.584
[ Ringing ]

18:05.793 --> 18:07.795
Operator: 911.
What's your emergency?

18:09.046 --> 18:11.132
My neighbor keeps an illegal
firearm under his bed.

18:11.132 --> 18:12.883
I'm in fear for my life.
Send the police.

18:12.883 --> 18:14.385
70 Oak Place.

18:14.385 --> 18:20.516
♪♪

18:20.516 --> 18:22.059
Ken: I don't remember
his face.

18:22.059 --> 18:25.146
I keep trying, but, uh,
every time I try and focus,

18:25.146 --> 18:28.107
uh, it just skitters away
from me like a silverfish.

18:28.107 --> 18:31.068
Well, that's your mind
protecting you.

18:31.068 --> 18:32.194
It's normal.

18:32.194 --> 18:34.447
Yet I remember him
acting so horrified

18:34.447 --> 18:36.907
that he hit me
with his car.

18:36.907 --> 18:40.077
He insisted on taking me
to the hospital, so...

18:41.454 --> 18:43.539
...I let him put me
in the back seat.

18:43.539 --> 18:45.207
Just went along with it.

18:45.207 --> 18:46.792
A stranger said
he was gonna help me,

18:46.792 --> 18:48.169
and I trusted him.

18:48.169 --> 18:49.920
Of course you did.

18:49.920 --> 18:52.923
Anyone else
would've done the same.

18:52.923 --> 18:54.634
Did he say anything
in the car?

18:54.634 --> 18:55.885
I‐I don't remember.

18:55.885 --> 18:59.096
I‐I blacked out as soon
as I got into the car.

18:59.096 --> 19:00.973
Well, they found Rohypnol
in your system.

19:00.973 --> 19:02.808
That would explain
the blackout.

19:02.808 --> 19:04.352
Do you remember anything

19:04.352 --> 19:06.604
from inside
the abandoned building

19:06.604 --> 19:07.730
where he took you?

19:07.730 --> 19:11.442
Unfortunately, um,
when I woke up...

19:12.818 --> 19:14.779
...pain was
just eating me alive,

19:14.779 --> 19:19.033
and, uh, I remember praying
that I would black out.

19:19.033 --> 19:22.161
And then he started stomping
on my broken legs.

19:22.161 --> 19:24.330
Is there anything else
you remember?

19:24.330 --> 19:25.831
The smallest thing
could help.

19:25.831 --> 19:27.792
Uh, his back.

19:27.792 --> 19:30.628
At one point, he leaned over,
and his shirt came up,

19:30.628 --> 19:32.088
and there was something
on his back.

19:32.088 --> 19:34.799
Was it a tattoo?
Scar?

19:34.799 --> 19:36.092
Uh, ma‐‐
Uh, maybe a burn?

19:36.092 --> 19:37.885
I don't think
it's a tattoo.

19:37.885 --> 19:39.637
Maybe a burn or a scar.

19:39.637 --> 19:41.138
Does that help?

19:41.138 --> 19:42.306
Absolutely.

19:42.306 --> 19:44.266
Um, call us

19:44.266 --> 19:46.143
if you can think
of anything else,

19:46.143 --> 19:48.688
and I will be sure to keep you
up to date on the case.

19:48.688 --> 19:49.730
Okay?

19:49.730 --> 19:51.023
Thank you.
Yeah.

19:51.857 --> 19:53.651
Hey,
this guy is a predator.

19:53.651 --> 19:56.362
He knew exactly
how to incapacitate you.

19:57.697 --> 19:59.490
What happened
was not your fault.

20:08.874 --> 20:10.793
You made sure
you weren't followed?
Yes.

20:10.793 --> 20:13.254
I drove around in circles
for like a half an hour.

20:17.466 --> 20:19.176
So, how does this work?

20:19.176 --> 20:20.970
Well, that's up to you.

20:20.970 --> 20:23.514
Your ad indicated you have
a problem with your husband?

20:23.514 --> 20:24.598
Yes.

20:24.598 --> 20:26.434
I need him to not be
alive anymore.

20:26.434 --> 20:27.643
Mm, that's not
gonna be enough.

20:27.643 --> 20:29.520
We need her to spell it out.
Okay.

20:29.520 --> 20:31.313
Do you want it to look like
natural causes?

20:31.313 --> 20:32.940
A suicide? Homicide?

20:32.940 --> 20:35.234
Must be a lonely kind
of life ‐‐

20:35.234 --> 20:36.694
being a hitman.

20:36.694 --> 20:38.320
[ Clicks tongue ]
It can be.

20:38.320 --> 20:39.822
So, you're not
seeing anyone?

20:39.822 --> 20:41.907
Oh, my God.
She's hitting on you.

20:41.907 --> 20:43.743
No, not at the moment.

20:43.743 --> 20:44.910
Mm.
You see, the thing is,

20:44.910 --> 20:47.747
the fee varies
depending on the method.

20:47.747 --> 20:50.624
So I need you to tell me
what you want.

20:50.624 --> 20:52.626
[ Inhales sharply ]
Ooh.

20:52.626 --> 20:56.547
What I want changed a little
when you got in the car.

20:56.547 --> 20:58.466
Wait, is she touching you?
She's touching you, isn't she?

20:58.466 --> 20:59.467
Hey, you know what?

20:59.467 --> 21:00.634
If she offers you money
for sex,

21:00.634 --> 21:02.094
I'm gonna win this bet.

21:02.094 --> 21:06.432
Look, I am down
to do whatever you want.
Hmm.

21:06.432 --> 21:08.893
Yeah, you are.
I just want to get the business
out of the way first.

21:10.060 --> 21:12.521
So, it's $20,000
for a straight murder ‐‐

21:12.521 --> 21:15.107
$25,000 if you want it
to look like suicide.

21:16.275 --> 21:17.443
Sexy.

21:17.443 --> 21:20.488
I'd pay you twice that
to kill the bastard.

21:22.406 --> 21:23.783
And the bastard is?

21:23.783 --> 21:26.035
My husband, obviously.

21:26.035 --> 21:27.161
Yes. Got her.

21:27.161 --> 21:29.121
You know, once he's dead,

21:29.121 --> 21:31.874
I'll be a very wealthy woman.

21:31.874 --> 21:33.501
Hmm.

21:33.501 --> 21:35.085
You're under arrest.

21:35.085 --> 21:37.046
All right. No, I‐I appreciate
the help.

21:37.046 --> 21:38.964
Thank you. Bye.

21:38.964 --> 21:40.591
Hey. Anything?

21:40.591 --> 21:42.510
We struck out
with Fred's gardener.

21:42.510 --> 21:44.053
He has access
to Fred's property,

21:44.053 --> 21:46.263
but he has an alibi
for almost every murder.

21:46.263 --> 21:47.598
He's definitely not
our guy.

21:47.598 --> 21:50.142
And the mail carrier
alibied out, too.

21:50.142 --> 21:51.644
So, that leaves us with...

21:51.644 --> 21:52.686
The handyman.

21:54.396 --> 21:56.482
His name's Ricardo Fuentes,

21:56.482 --> 21:58.526
and he has a couple of
assault charges from years ago.

21:58.526 --> 22:00.861
Did you talk with him?
Yeah, and he was
less than helpful.

22:00.861 --> 22:03.239
When I asked for his whereabouts
on the dates of the murders,

22:03.239 --> 22:04.698
he refused to answer.

22:04.698 --> 22:05.908
That doesn't make him
a suspect.

22:05.908 --> 22:08.327
I mean, maybe he just
doesn't trust the police.

22:08.327 --> 22:10.496
True,
but when I asked him

22:10.496 --> 22:12.414
why he went to Fred's house
yesterday morning,

22:12.414 --> 22:14.083
he had an odd answer.

22:14.083 --> 22:15.876
He said he got a call
to go to Fred's house

22:15.876 --> 22:17.336
to strap
the water heater down

22:17.336 --> 22:18.629
and that he was told
to enter the property

22:18.629 --> 22:19.922
if no one was home.

22:19.922 --> 22:21.090
And the odd part is?

22:21.090 --> 22:22.424
How he claims he was paid.

22:22.424 --> 22:24.635
With cash, in an envelope
taped to the water heater.

22:24.635 --> 22:26.136
But of course,
he threw away the envelope.

22:26.136 --> 22:27.680
So, maybe he's
telling the truth,

22:27.680 --> 22:29.890
and this is him going
to strap down the water heater.

22:29.890 --> 22:31.976
Or he's setting the bomb
that killed Fred.

22:31.976 --> 22:33.644
Okay, well,
that's easily verifiable.

22:33.644 --> 22:36.021
I can just swing by Fred's house
on the way home,

22:36.021 --> 22:37.231
see if Ricardo
did the work.

22:37.231 --> 22:38.732
Thanks.
Let us know what you find.

22:38.732 --> 22:40.109
You got it.

22:40.109 --> 22:41.110
[ Sighs ]

22:41.110 --> 22:43.070
[ Dog barking ]

22:43.904 --> 22:45.739
[ Liquid pouring ]

22:45.739 --> 22:47.616
Hey, where's the food?

22:47.616 --> 22:49.535
[ Keys clatter ]
[ Sighs ]

22:49.535 --> 22:51.328
I forgot.

22:51.328 --> 22:52.997
Sorry. It's been
a crazy day.

22:52.997 --> 22:54.707
Which is why I said
we should order in,

22:54.707 --> 22:55.875
but you insisted

22:55.875 --> 22:57.167
that you would be
driving by the restaurant

22:57.167 --> 22:58.127
and would
pick something up.

22:58.127 --> 22:59.253
Okay, I forgot.

22:59.253 --> 23:01.547
Okay?
Cut me some slack.
Slack?

23:01.547 --> 23:04.383
I work just as long as you
but somehow still came home,

23:04.383 --> 23:06.760
tidied up the house, fed Jack,
and put him to bed.

23:06.760 --> 23:08.012
Well, that's because
you're perfect.

23:08.012 --> 23:09.138
The rest of us
are just human.

23:09.138 --> 23:10.472
Wow. Where did that
come from?

23:10.472 --> 23:11.807
[ Door opens ]
Where are you going?

23:11.807 --> 23:13.893
To get the food.

23:13.893 --> 23:15.853
[ Door slams ]
[ Jack crying ]

23:15.853 --> 23:17.479
[ Insects chirping ]

23:17.479 --> 23:19.523
[ Dog barking in distance ]

23:19.523 --> 23:21.567
♪♪

23:25.195 --> 23:27.740
[ Sighs ]

23:27.740 --> 23:28.782
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

23:28.782 --> 23:30.326
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hey.

23:30.326 --> 23:31.368
Bailey: When are you
coming home?

23:31.368 --> 23:33.579
You okay?
Yeah, I'm just tired.

23:33.579 --> 23:35.247
These painkillers
are no joke.

23:35.247 --> 23:36.457
Don't wait up for me.

23:36.457 --> 23:38.125
Go to sleep.
How's it going?

23:38.125 --> 23:39.960
We're gonna catch this guy.
I promise.

23:39.960 --> 23:41.754
Oh, don't do that.

23:41.754 --> 23:43.380
I don't need
empty promises.

23:43.380 --> 23:45.132
It's bad for relationships.

23:45.132 --> 23:46.383
Trust me.
Okay.

23:46.383 --> 23:48.510
Well, we had a suspect,
but his story checks out,

23:48.510 --> 23:50.054
and now we got nothing.

23:50.054 --> 23:52.681
Well, there's three
varieties of pie

23:52.681 --> 23:54.391
waiting for you
when you get home.

23:54.391 --> 23:56.560
You are supposed to be
staying off your feet ‐‐

23:56.560 --> 23:58.228
and what kind of pie?

23:58.228 --> 24:00.189
Cherry, apple,
and chocolate cream.

24:00.189 --> 24:02.608
You're my favorite.
That's good,
'cause you're mine.

24:02.608 --> 24:04.276
Hurry home to me, okay?

24:04.276 --> 24:05.527
Yes, ma'am.

24:05.527 --> 24:07.071
[ Cellphone beeps ]

24:09.114 --> 24:11.116
Hey, Marcus.
Marcus: Nolan.

24:11.116 --> 24:12.868
Thanks again for that, uh,
doorbell footage.

24:12.868 --> 24:14.828
It helped.
Ah, good, good.

24:14.828 --> 24:16.455
Um, any leads?

24:16.455 --> 24:18.457
Uh, we're checking
all the angles.

24:20.918 --> 24:22.086
[ Metal clinks ]

24:22.086 --> 24:28.342
♪♪

24:28.342 --> 24:30.094
Well...

24:30.094 --> 24:31.345
have a good night.

24:31.345 --> 24:32.513
You too.

24:32.513 --> 24:40.437
♪♪

24:40.437 --> 24:42.022
[ Cellphone beeps ]

24:42.022 --> 24:44.817
[ Engine starts, tires screech ]

24:44.817 --> 24:47.236
♪♪

24:47.236 --> 24:48.570
Ugh!

24:48.570 --> 24:50.823
[ Nolan groans ]

24:50.823 --> 24:55.828
♪♪

24:55.828 --> 24:57.830
[ Spray hisses ]

24:57.830 --> 25:04.837
♪♪

25:08.674 --> 25:11.468
[ Harmonica music plays ]

25:11.468 --> 25:18.767
♪♪

25:18.767 --> 25:26.108
♪♪

25:26.108 --> 25:28.027
Hey there. [ Chuckles ]

25:28.027 --> 25:30.154
You were out
for quite a while.

25:30.154 --> 25:32.906
You know, mixing Rohypnol
and head trauma

25:32.906 --> 25:34.616
can be a little...

25:34.616 --> 25:36.118
dicey.

25:36.118 --> 25:38.370
Nolan: Where...
[ Voice echoing ]
...are you?

25:38.370 --> 25:41.540
[ Chuckles ] Only the coolest
place in Los Angeles.

25:41.540 --> 25:42.791
I found this place
when I was out looking

25:42.791 --> 25:43.959
for a new killing ground.

25:43.959 --> 25:45.294
It's some kind
of used factory.

25:45.294 --> 25:47.588
I don't know what the hell
they made here, but it is huge

25:47.588 --> 25:49.506
and super abandoned,

25:49.506 --> 25:52.634
and it got me thinking
on a much larger scale.

25:52.634 --> 25:54.344
♪♪

25:54.344 --> 25:56.221
Hey, John?

25:56.221 --> 25:57.431
John.

26:00.851 --> 26:03.437
[ Screams ]

26:03.437 --> 26:04.813
There you go.

26:04.813 --> 26:05.898
[ Groans ]

26:05.898 --> 26:07.608
Hey.

26:07.608 --> 26:11.445
Do you know what
the adductor longus is, John?

26:11.445 --> 26:12.571
Oh, probably not.

26:12.571 --> 26:16.283
Uh, I'm pretty sure
yours is shredded.

26:16.283 --> 26:18.702
You know,
when car hits human,

26:18.702 --> 26:20.287
human always loses.

26:20.287 --> 26:21.705
But who am I
to tell you that?

26:21.705 --> 26:23.916
I mean,
how many car wrecks

26:23.916 --> 26:25.626
and hit‐and‐runs
have you worked?

26:25.626 --> 26:26.919
They're gonna catch you.

26:26.919 --> 26:28.545
Maybe.

26:28.545 --> 26:30.047
I mean, you ‐‐

26:30.047 --> 26:32.049
you got
uncomfortably close ‐‐

26:32.049 --> 26:34.968
closer than anyone
ever has.

26:34.968 --> 26:36.345
It's all my fault.

26:36.345 --> 26:37.930
No, I got lazy.

26:37.930 --> 26:42.101
For 10 years, I have had
an ironclad MO ‐‐

26:42.101 --> 26:43.727
travel to hunt.

26:43.727 --> 26:46.897
But I‐I figured, you know,
Los Angeles, it's so big.

26:46.897 --> 26:48.148
I‐I figured if I stayed

26:48.148 --> 26:50.150
far enough away
from where I lived,

26:50.150 --> 26:52.986
it'd be kind of like
a‐a murder staycation.

26:52.986 --> 26:57.366
But then you got lucky
with that hot firefighter,

26:57.366 --> 26:58.909
and I got unlucky.

26:58.909 --> 27:03.288
So, it's time
to leave "Marcus" behind,

27:03.288 --> 27:06.750
get off the grid,
go on the run.

27:06.750 --> 27:09.503
But, you know, first, I thought
I'd have a little fun.

27:09.503 --> 27:10.671
[ Laughs ]

27:10.671 --> 27:12.798
[ Coughing ]

27:12.798 --> 27:14.341
Would you stop trying
to break free?

27:14.341 --> 27:16.927
I'm gonna let you go
in a minute.

27:16.927 --> 27:19.304
Bull.
No, really.

27:19.304 --> 27:21.557
See, the thing
about addicts is,

27:21.557 --> 27:23.809
they're constantly trying
to relive that first high ‐‐

27:23.809 --> 27:25.227
you know, when the effect
was the strongest.

27:25.227 --> 27:27.604
It's just ‐‐ It's never
as good the second time.

27:27.604 --> 27:30.190
Is that why you target
former addicts?

27:30.190 --> 27:32.234
Trying to punish
a version of yourself?

27:32.234 --> 27:33.360
[ Laughs ]

27:33.360 --> 27:34.987
God, no!

27:34.987 --> 27:37.823
I feel no shame
for what I do.

27:37.823 --> 27:39.741
The needs I feel.

27:39.741 --> 27:43.161
No, if I could
murder someone every day,

27:43.161 --> 27:46.582
I would be the happiest man
on the planet.

27:46.582 --> 27:48.500
Oh, I don't know ‐‐
maybe I'd lose my taste for it.

27:48.500 --> 27:50.586
You know, like when you eat
too many chips.

27:50.586 --> 27:52.462
Anybody ever tell you
you're crazy?

27:52.462 --> 27:54.131
Sure.

27:54.131 --> 27:55.799
But then
I burn them to ash.

27:55.799 --> 27:58.010
[ Breathing heavily ]

27:59.136 --> 28:00.470
[ Mumbles ]

28:00.470 --> 28:01.763
Ah.

28:03.807 --> 28:05.475
[ Both grunting ]

28:05.475 --> 28:07.185
♪♪

28:07.185 --> 28:08.395
[ Whooping ]

28:08.395 --> 28:10.022
Ooh, that was close.

28:10.022 --> 28:12.065
Ooh, I should've
seen that coming.

28:12.065 --> 28:15.694
[ Laughs ] Okay,
not a great first step.

28:15.694 --> 28:17.696
We'll call it
a useful failing.

28:17.696 --> 28:20.115
A teachable moment.

28:20.115 --> 28:22.618
[ Exhales sharply ]

28:24.119 --> 28:25.787
Now...

28:25.787 --> 28:27.080
here's the deal.

28:28.582 --> 28:30.334
I'm gonna cut you free.

28:30.334 --> 28:32.753
I'm gonna give you
a one‐minute head start,

28:32.753 --> 28:34.671
and then I'm gonna
come kill you.

28:34.671 --> 28:36.340
You gonna give me a weapon?

28:36.340 --> 28:38.592
[ Chuckles ]
I said I wanted a challenge,

28:38.592 --> 28:40.510
but I'm not an idiot.

28:40.510 --> 28:42.512
And what if I don't run?

28:42.512 --> 28:44.348
What if I come over there
and I take that knife

28:44.348 --> 28:46.183
and I stick it someplace
you don't like?

28:47.392 --> 28:48.685
Aah!

28:48.685 --> 28:50.020
[ Grunts ]

28:52.272 --> 28:53.273
[ Grunts ]

28:53.273 --> 28:55.442
♪♪

28:55.442 --> 28:56.860
Well,
I think we're ready.

28:56.860 --> 28:58.654
Huh?

28:58.654 --> 29:00.739
This is exciting.
[ Chuckles ]

29:00.739 --> 29:02.741
I'm ‐‐ I'm actually
a little bit nervous.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.701
Are ‐‐ Are you?

29:04.701 --> 29:07.913
Well, ready, set...

29:07.913 --> 29:08.997
♪♪

29:08.997 --> 29:11.249
[ Laughs ] Oops.

29:11.249 --> 29:14.086
I mean, you didn't think
I'd play fair, did you?

29:14.086 --> 29:15.462
[ Heartbeat ]

29:15.462 --> 29:18.465
[ Echoing ] All right, well,
a‐one‐a‐Mississippi.

29:19.549 --> 29:22.427
A‐two‐a‐Mississippi.
[ Grunting, panting ]

29:22.427 --> 29:24.471
Tha‐ree‐a‐Mississippi.

29:25.889 --> 29:28.141
[ Groaning ]

29:28.141 --> 29:35.941
♪♪

29:35.941 --> 29:38.485
[ Harmonica playing
soulful tune ]

29:41.363 --> 29:42.906
[ Grunting ]

29:42.906 --> 29:50.706
♪♪

29:50.706 --> 29:53.834
[ Gags, vomits ]

29:53.834 --> 29:54.793
[ Spits ]

29:54.793 --> 29:57.546
[ Gasping ]

29:57.546 --> 29:59.923
[ Shouts ]

29:59.923 --> 30:02.926
♪♪

30:02.926 --> 30:04.928
[ Harmonica continues playing ]

30:04.928 --> 30:14.563
♪♪

30:14.563 --> 30:24.239
♪♪

30:24.239 --> 30:33.874
♪♪

30:33.874 --> 30:35.500
[ Grunting ]

30:35.500 --> 30:43.633
♪♪

30:43.633 --> 30:51.850
♪♪

30:51.850 --> 30:53.143
Marcus: John?

30:53.143 --> 30:58.648
♪♪

30:58.648 --> 30:59.900
[ Chuckles ]

30:59.900 --> 31:01.693
Well...

31:01.693 --> 31:04.863
This is fun, isn't it?

31:04.863 --> 31:06.948
I gotta say, the silence?

31:06.948 --> 31:08.366
It's kinda nice.

31:08.366 --> 31:11.536
Usually, there's a lot
of whining and begging.

31:11.536 --> 31:13.371
Fair amount of sobbing.

31:13.371 --> 31:16.374
I mean, you'd think
that would be part of my thrill,

31:16.374 --> 31:19.461
but, you know, it really
just works on the nerves.

31:19.461 --> 31:20.837
[ Metal clatters ]
[ Gunshot ]

31:20.837 --> 31:22.172
[ Steam hissing ]

31:22.172 --> 31:24.216
♪♪

31:24.216 --> 31:26.051
[ Gunshots ]

31:26.051 --> 31:35.602
♪♪

31:35.602 --> 31:37.312
[ Groaning ]

31:37.312 --> 31:41.191
♪♪

31:41.191 --> 31:42.901
[ Door creaks ]

31:42.901 --> 31:51.743
♪♪

31:51.743 --> 32:00.585
♪♪

32:00.585 --> 32:02.379
Whoo‐hoo‐hoo‐hoo!

32:02.379 --> 32:03.672
John.

32:03.672 --> 32:06.550
[ Pipes clattering ]

32:06.550 --> 32:09.094
[ Grunts ]
See, the thing is,

32:09.094 --> 32:10.762
the deck is stacked
against you.

32:10.762 --> 32:13.682
You see, I've had weeks
to get this place ready.

32:14.766 --> 32:16.768
Hey, here we go.

32:16.768 --> 32:19.688
♪♪

32:19.688 --> 32:21.356
[ Grunting ]

32:23.108 --> 32:24.776
[ Marcus laughs evilly ]

32:28.488 --> 32:29.531
What's wrong, John?
You stuck?

32:29.531 --> 32:30.991
[ Grunting ]

32:30.991 --> 32:36.788
♪♪

32:36.788 --> 32:38.623
Run, rabbit! Run!

32:38.623 --> 32:41.084
[ Grunting ]

32:41.084 --> 32:42.419
Agh!
[ Inhales sharply ]

32:42.419 --> 32:52.179
♪♪

32:52.179 --> 32:54.306
Whoo‐hoo‐hoo!
John!

32:54.306 --> 32:55.307
[ Grunts ]

32:55.307 --> 32:59.352
♪♪

32:59.352 --> 33:02.063
[ Grunts, chuckles ]

33:02.063 --> 33:06.735
♪♪

33:06.735 --> 33:09.446
[ Marcus chuckles ]

33:09.446 --> 33:19.164
♪♪

33:19.164 --> 33:20.498
[ Pounding on door ]

33:20.498 --> 33:28.965
♪♪

33:28.965 --> 33:30.300
[ Shell clatters ]

33:30.300 --> 33:36.890
♪♪

33:36.890 --> 33:43.521
♪♪

33:43.521 --> 33:44.898
[ Drawer clacks ]

33:44.898 --> 33:50.028
♪♪

33:50.028 --> 33:51.529
Hey, John.

33:51.529 --> 33:59.496
♪♪

33:59.496 --> 34:01.331
John, you in there?

34:01.331 --> 34:02.832
Hey, you wanna know
a little secret?

34:02.832 --> 34:04.584
I hate scary movies.

34:04.584 --> 34:06.294
I mean, you'd think
I'd love them 'cause ‐‐

34:06.294 --> 34:07.629
well, duh.

34:07.629 --> 34:10.674
But no, I'm actually a sucker
for a jump‐scare.

34:10.674 --> 34:14.052
You know, the way ‐‐ the way
you get everything real quiet.

34:15.512 --> 34:18.848
And then it gets you
on the edge of your seat.

34:18.848 --> 34:19.891
You know.

34:19.891 --> 34:21.142
And then ‐‐ bam!

34:21.142 --> 34:25.021
♪♪

34:25.021 --> 34:26.690
[ Laughs ]
[ Shotgun cocks ]

34:26.690 --> 34:28.316
♪♪

34:28.316 --> 34:30.694
[ Shotgun clicks ]
Ugh!

34:30.694 --> 34:33.405
♪♪

34:33.405 --> 34:35.115
[ Grunting ]

34:35.115 --> 34:38.285
♪♪

34:38.285 --> 34:39.619
[ Both grunting ]

34:40.704 --> 34:42.247
Ugh!

34:42.247 --> 34:44.249
[ Groans ]

34:45.875 --> 34:48.753
[ Grunts, spits ]

34:48.753 --> 34:55.260
♪♪

34:55.260 --> 34:57.053
Argh.

34:57.053 --> 34:59.681
♪♪

34:59.681 --> 35:02.017
It's over, Marcus!

35:02.017 --> 35:03.310
Give it up!

35:03.310 --> 35:05.312
We can still call you
an ambulance!

35:05.312 --> 35:06.730
You stabbed me.

35:06.730 --> 35:08.857
What the heck
did you stab me with?

35:08.857 --> 35:10.275
Scissors.

35:10.275 --> 35:11.943
Rusty ones, too.

35:11.943 --> 35:14.154
Now, you give your ass up.

35:14.154 --> 35:16.615
You make this
a fight to the death,

35:16.615 --> 35:18.325
I swear to God,

35:18.325 --> 35:20.410
you'll be the one
they carry out of here!
[ Gun cocks ]

35:20.410 --> 35:22.495
[ Laughs ]

35:22.495 --> 35:24.623
Aw, come on.

35:24.623 --> 35:25.624
[ Gun clicks ]

35:25.624 --> 35:27.709
Ah, safety,
safety, safety.

35:27.709 --> 35:28.835
[ Grunts ]

35:30.587 --> 35:36.926
♪♪

35:36.926 --> 35:38.595
[ Chuckling ]

35:38.595 --> 35:48.355
♪♪

35:48.355 --> 35:50.315
[ Grunting ]

35:50.315 --> 35:51.691
[ Engine sputters ]

35:53.276 --> 35:55.153
[ Engine starts ]

35:55.153 --> 35:56.571
Yes.

35:56.571 --> 36:02.077
♪♪

36:02.077 --> 36:03.995
[ Machine‐gun fire ]

36:03.995 --> 36:05.664
Agh!

36:05.664 --> 36:10.251
♪♪

36:10.251 --> 36:11.920
Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

36:11.920 --> 36:13.254
[ Growling ]

36:13.254 --> 36:17.884
♪♪

36:17.884 --> 36:20.095
Aw! [ Grunting ]

36:20.095 --> 36:24.140
♪♪

36:24.140 --> 36:25.475
[ Bullets ricocheting ]

36:29.646 --> 36:31.022
[ Ringing ]

36:31.022 --> 36:32.399
♪♪

36:32.399 --> 36:34.192
Operator: 911.
What's your emergency?

36:34.192 --> 36:37.779
This is Officer John Nolan,
badge number 25253.

36:37.779 --> 36:40.532
I am hurt and under attack
by Marcus Lindsey,

36:40.532 --> 36:42.951
a serial murder suspect
armed with an assault rifle.

36:42.951 --> 36:44.119
Send help!

36:44.119 --> 36:45.745
♪♪

36:45.745 --> 36:47.247
[ Engine revving ]

36:47.247 --> 36:51.418
♪♪

36:51.418 --> 36:54.754
♪♪

36:54.754 --> 36:56.005
[ Tires squeal ]

36:56.005 --> 37:02.303
♪♪

37:02.303 --> 37:04.013
[ Engine rattles, stops ]

37:13.314 --> 37:14.899
[ Groaning ]

37:19.946 --> 37:21.156
I win.

37:22.240 --> 37:23.742
And you're under arrest.

37:23.742 --> 37:25.243
[ Train horn blares
in distance ]

37:25.243 --> 37:35.044
♪♪

37:38.715 --> 37:39.883
[ Sighs ]

37:39.883 --> 37:42.969
Ugh! [ Coughing ]

37:42.969 --> 37:44.220
Moreno: Whoo.

37:44.220 --> 37:45.597
You need to pay
better attention

37:45.597 --> 37:46.890
to your surroundings, man.

37:46.890 --> 37:47.891
What do they call it?

37:47.891 --> 37:49.058
Uh...

37:49.058 --> 37:50.518
Situational awareness.

37:50.518 --> 37:52.520
Elijah's not gonna be
happy about this.

37:52.520 --> 37:54.481
Elijah brought his own bat.

37:54.481 --> 37:55.857
Wait, wait, wait!
Why are you doing this?!

37:55.857 --> 37:57.150
Stop! Stop!

38:00.028 --> 38:01.863
The strangest thing
happened yesterday

38:01.863 --> 38:03.990
after you left
that witness' home.

38:03.990 --> 38:05.867
♪♪

38:05.867 --> 38:07.702
Cops swooped in
and arrested him.

38:07.702 --> 38:09.662
It was almost like someone
wanted to keep him

38:09.662 --> 38:11.790
out of harm's way.

38:11.790 --> 38:13.583
It's like you were
working against me.

38:13.583 --> 38:14.876
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:14.876 --> 38:16.419
Are you really this stupid?

38:19.297 --> 38:21.424
[ Groans loudly ]

38:21.424 --> 38:22.467
[ Breathing heavily ]

38:22.467 --> 38:24.093
You told me
to make the witness go away.

38:24.093 --> 38:26.721
That's what I did!
I took him off the board!

38:27.847 --> 38:30.183
I got him arrested for
an illegal weapons violation.

38:30.183 --> 38:32.060
There is no way
he can testify now.

38:32.060 --> 38:33.770
His credibility's shot.

38:33.770 --> 38:34.854
And as an added bonus,

38:34.854 --> 38:37.065
you didn't have
to commit another crime.

38:37.065 --> 38:40.902
♪♪

38:40.902 --> 38:42.821
Oh.

38:42.821 --> 38:44.572
Well, that changes things.

38:44.572 --> 38:47.659
♪♪

38:47.659 --> 38:49.410
[ Breathing shakily ]

38:50.662 --> 38:53.248
You need to work on
your communication skills,

38:53.248 --> 38:56.543
'cause this beating's based
on your lack of transparency.

38:56.543 --> 38:58.169
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:58.169 --> 39:01.840
♪♪

39:01.840 --> 39:03.883
Are we good?

39:03.883 --> 39:05.677
Yeah.

39:05.677 --> 39:06.719
For now.

39:08.513 --> 39:09.681
Great work.

39:09.681 --> 39:12.517
♪♪

39:12.517 --> 39:13.935
[ Sniffs ]

39:13.935 --> 39:16.020
♪♪

39:16.020 --> 39:17.939
[ Monitor beeping ]

39:17.939 --> 39:20.358
[ Keys tapping ]

39:20.358 --> 39:22.527
Hey.

39:22.527 --> 39:23.528
Hey.

39:24.696 --> 39:27.574
Welcome back to the land
of the living.

39:27.574 --> 39:29.117
Doc said you were
pretty banged up,

39:29.117 --> 39:31.619
but lucky you ‐‐
no broken bones.

39:31.619 --> 39:33.079
Really?

39:33.079 --> 39:34.664
It feels like
everything's broken.

39:34.664 --> 39:36.416
[ Chuckles ]
They have meds for that.

39:36.416 --> 39:38.293
[ Chuckles ]

39:38.293 --> 39:39.794
Great job out there.

39:39.794 --> 39:40.962
We got him.

39:40.962 --> 39:42.088
No, you got him.

39:42.088 --> 39:44.674
Yeah, after he got me.

39:44.674 --> 39:47.719
[ Sighs ]

39:47.719 --> 39:49.387
There she is.

39:49.387 --> 39:50.847
Hi.

39:52.390 --> 39:54.559
♪ I was gonna do my makeup... ♪

39:54.559 --> 39:56.227
[ Sighs ]
Come here.

39:57.186 --> 39:58.855
Ow.
Oh, sorry.

39:58.855 --> 40:00.064
No, no.
It's okay, it's okay.

40:00.064 --> 40:01.774
It's a good hurt.
I can take it.

40:01.774 --> 40:03.026
I can take it.

40:03.026 --> 40:04.235
I can't take it.

40:04.235 --> 40:06.404
Mm.
[ Groans ]

40:06.404 --> 40:08.740
[ Sighs ]
I'm so relieved
you're okay.

40:08.740 --> 40:09.866
Oh, it's nothing.

40:09.866 --> 40:11.326
Just a couple more
war wounds

40:11.326 --> 40:13.244
I can flaunt in bed.

40:13.244 --> 40:14.913
Speaking of,
what are you doing here?

40:14.913 --> 40:16.205
Aren't you supposed
to be in bed?

40:16.205 --> 40:18.374
Mm, yeah.

40:18.374 --> 40:19.626
Scoot over.

40:19.626 --> 40:21.210
Done.

40:21.210 --> 40:23.004
[ Groans ]
Okay.

40:23.004 --> 40:24.756
♪ A house divided ♪

40:24.756 --> 40:25.882
Okay.

40:25.882 --> 40:29.469
♪ You left me
all ignited again ♪

40:29.469 --> 40:31.262
[ Both sigh ]

40:33.181 --> 40:35.058
You got him.

40:35.058 --> 40:36.517
I told you I would.

40:36.517 --> 40:38.061
[ Laughs ] Oh, no.

40:38.061 --> 40:40.063
"I told you so"
is so much worse

40:40.063 --> 40:41.147
than "I promise."

40:41.147 --> 40:43.524
Really?
A relationship killer.

40:43.524 --> 40:45.193
100%.

40:45.193 --> 40:47.570
I'm gonna need some kind
of cheat sheet, I think.

40:47.570 --> 40:49.155
[ Chuckles ]

40:49.155 --> 40:52.033
♪ Oh, oh ♪

40:52.033 --> 40:53.076
Seriously, I can't believe

40:53.076 --> 40:54.577
you bought out
the entire gift shop.

40:54.577 --> 40:56.454
What? You've been
in the hospital before.

40:56.454 --> 40:58.289
You know how boring
it can be.

40:58.289 --> 41:00.333
What did you get him?
Nothing.

41:00.333 --> 41:02.418
I'll just put my name
on yours.

41:02.418 --> 41:03.920
Unbelievable.

41:03.920 --> 41:05.088
Hey, we're going
back out on patrol

41:05.088 --> 41:06.965
after we're done visiting
with Nolan, right?

41:06.965 --> 41:08.091
[ Sighs ] Lucy.

41:08.091 --> 41:09.926
Mm‐hmm. What?

41:09.926 --> 41:11.344
You know,
I have a bet to win.

41:11.344 --> 41:12.595
Okay, can we just
call it off?

41:12.595 --> 41:14.472
Police work is too important
to turn into a game.

41:14.472 --> 41:16.265
You're just worried
you're gonna lose.

41:16.265 --> 41:18.351
Sure. If that's what you need to
hear, let's go with that.

41:18.351 --> 41:19.602
Wait, hold on.

41:19.602 --> 41:22.647
Since when did you become
the noble one here?

41:22.647 --> 41:24.983
Does this mean
we're square on our bet?

41:24.983 --> 41:26.067
Fine.

41:26.067 --> 41:27.276
Nobody wins.

41:27.276 --> 41:29.445
But the basket
is only from me.

41:29.445 --> 41:32.490
♪♪

41:32.490 --> 41:34.325
[ Door opens ]

41:36.119 --> 41:37.161
Where you been?

41:37.161 --> 41:39.080
I thought you were gonna
be here for bedtime.

41:41.582 --> 41:43.626
Sorry, I‐I got stuck
on a call.

41:53.511 --> 41:55.221
[ Exhales sharply ]
Angela.

41:58.558 --> 42:04.188
♪♪

42:04.188 --> 42:06.649
What's wrong?

42:06.649 --> 42:08.317
[ Voice breaking ]
I screwed up.

42:09.861 --> 42:11.279
I need help.

42:11.279 --> 42:13.906
♪♪

42:13.906 --> 42:14.907
[ Sighs shakily ]

42:18.286 --> 42:27.295
♪♪

42:27.295 --> 42:36.345
♪♪

42:36.345 --> 42:45.396
♪♪
